<section class="slide-sources">
  <h2>Superconducting sources</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>Substrate induced</h3>
    <p>
      $$
      V =
      - \sum_{\mathbf{k} \nu \tau} \Delta_{\nu}
      {d^{\nu}_{\tau}}^{\dagger} \left( \mathbf{k} \right)
      d^{\nu}_{-\tau} \left( \mathbf{k} \right)
      $$
    </p>
    <p>⇒ Intervalley pairing</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Intrinsic (density-density interaction)</h3>
    <p>
      $$
      V =
      \frac{1}{2} \sum_{\mathbf{R} \mathbf{R'}}
      v_{\mathbf{R} \mathbf{R'}}
      :n_{\mathbf{R}} n_{\mathbf{R'}}:
      $$
    </p>
    <p>Assume even pairing interaction &amp; mean field</p>
    <p>⇒ Intravalley and intervalley pairing</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="slide-channels">
  <h2>Superconducting channels</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Project into upper-valance bands (\( \tau = s \))</li>
    <li>Mean field theory BCS-type solutions:
        order parameter \( \Delta_{\mathbf{k}} \)</li>
    <li>\( m = 0 \) <strong>intervalley</strong> channel always dominates</li>
    <li>Both classes give <strong>constant order parameter </strong>
        for dominant paring</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Induced</h3>
  <p>
    $$
    \Delta_{\mathbf{k}} =
    \frac{1}{2} \left( \Delta_+ + \Delta_- \right)
    - \frac{1}{2} \left( \Delta_+ - \Delta_- \right)
    \cos{\theta_{\mathbf{k}}}
    $$
  </p>
  <h3>Intrinsic</h3>
  <p>
    $$
    \Delta_{\mathbf{k}} =
    g_{\mathbf{k}}
    v_0 \sum_{\mathbf{k}'}
    g^*_{\mathbf{k}'}
    \langle c_{-\mathbf{k}' \alpha'} c_{\mathbf{k}' \alpha} \rangle
    $$
  </p>
</section>

